<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="PA-changing-quadratic">

<statement>
	<p>
		A water balloon is tossed vertically from a fifth story window.  Its height, <m>h</m>, in meters, at time <m>t</m>, in seconds, is modeled by the function
		<me>
			h = q(t) = -5t^2 + 20t + 25
		</me>.
	</p>

	<p>
		<ol label="a.">
			<li>
				<p>
					Execute appropriate computations to complete both of the following tables.  
				</p>
				<sidebyside width="50%">
					<table xml:id="T-PA-changing-quadratic-heights">
						<caption>Function values for <m>h</m> at select inputs.</caption>
						<tabular>
							<row bottom="minor">
								<cell><m>t</m></cell>
								<cell><m>h = q(t)</m></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>0</m></cell>
								<cell><m>q(0) = 25</m></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>1</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>2</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>3</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>4</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>5</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
						</tabular>
					</table>	
					<table xml:id="T-PA-changing-quadratic-AVs">
						<caption>Average rates of change for <m>h</m> on select intervals.</caption>
						<tabular>
							<row bottom="minor">
								<cell><m>[a,b]</m></cell>
								<cell><m>AV_{[a,b]}</m></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>[0,1]</m></cell>
								<cell><m>AV_{[0,1]} = 15</m> m/s</cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>[1,2]</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>[2,3]</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>[3,4]</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>[4,5]</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
						</tabular>
					</table>
				</sidebyside>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					What pattern(s) do you observe in <xref ref="T-PA-changing-quadratic-heights">Tables</xref> and <xref ref="T-PA-changing-quadratic-AVs"/>?
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					Explain why <m>h = q(t)</m> is not a linear function.  Use <xref ref="D-linear-function">Definition</xref> in your response.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					What is the average velocity of the water balloon in the final second before it lands?  How does this value compare to the average velocity on the time interval <m>[4.9, 5]</m>?
				</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
	</p>
</statement>

</exploration>